data.description: Beautifully renovated 2 bedroom, 2 full bath concrete bungalow with Old Seminole Heights charm combined with modern touches. Everything is new! As you step inside from the front porch, you’ll notice the brand new solid hardwood floors that lead to the fully remodeled kitchen in this open & split floorpan. The kitchen includes new high-end, stainless steel appliances with granite countertops with a large peninsula overseeing the living area. The entire house is naturally lit with brand new double pane windows throughout and cooled with a brand new HVAC system. The hallway leads to a bedroom in either direction with a completely upgraded bathroom towards the 2nd bedroom and a huge master bath in the master bedroom.  From the kitchen you’ll pass through the tiled laundry room perfect for a stackable washer/dryer and out the back door to the fully fenced back yard, perfect for BBQ’s and family gatherings with more than enough room to add a pool. There is also a newer storage shed located in the back yard. The roof was replaced in 2021, as was the AC, water heater, all new plumbing, windows, flooring, and just about everything else. WDO report attached. Conveniently located near stores and restaurants, about a mile to I-275 and within minutes to I-4, downtown, & close to everything Tampa has to offer. With all these features, don't miss out this house will go fast!
